        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 25 at 8:22PM CDT until May 25 at 9:00PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 822 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 3 miles southwest of Boys Ranch to 6 miles south of
Wildorado, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.

Locations impacted include...
Wildorado.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with these storms, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
